title: US clings to 1-point lead in Presidents Cup
text: National US clings to 1-point lead in Presidents Cup                 International team player Branden Grace of South Africa plays from a bunker on the eighth hole during his four ball match at the Presidents Cup golf tournament at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, in Incheon, South Korea, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015.(AP Photo/Lee Jin-man) United States' Jordan Spieth reacts after sinking a putt on the 18th green to win their foursome match at the Presidents Cup golf tournament at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, in Incheon, South Korea, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015.(AP Photo/Lee Jin-man) United States' Phil Mickelson plays a chip into the 11th green during his four ball match at the Presidents Cup golf tournament at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, in Incheon, South Korea, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015.(AP Photo/Woohae Cho) International team player Adam Scott, right, of Australia and his playing partner Anirban Lahiri of India line up a putt on the 10th hole during their four ball match at the Presidents Cup golf tournament at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, in Incheon, South Korea, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015.(AP Photo/Lee Jin-man) United States' Phil Mickelson hits off the 11th tee during his four ball match at the Presidents Cup golf tournament at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, in Incheon, South Korea, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015.(AP Photo/Woohae Cho) United States' J.B. Holmes, left, and teammate Bubba Watson celebrate on the ninth hole during their four ball match at the Presidents Cup golf tournament at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, in Incheon, South Korea, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015.(AP Photo/Lee Jin-man) International team player Sangmoon Bae of South Korea walks to the fifth green during his foursome match at the Presidents Cup golf tournament at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, in Incheon, South Korea, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015.(AP Photo/Lee Jin-man) International team player Hedeki Matsuyama of Japan hits off the first tee during his foursome match at the Presidents Cup golf tournament at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, in Incheon, South Korea, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015.(AP Photo/Lee Jin-man) By Doug Ferguson,   Oct. 10, 2015 4:34 a.m.
